#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code sliding window + HashMap use karta hai longest subarray nikalne ke liye
jisme at most 2 different fruits ho.

1. Do pointers use hue hain:
   - l = window start
   - r = window end
2. Jaise hi new fruit window me aata hai, uski frequency map me increase kar dete hain.
3. Agar map.size() > 2 ho gaya,
   matlab 2 se zyada fruit types aa gaye,
   to left side se window shrink karte hain.
4. Shrink karte time fruits[l] ki frequency kam karte hain,
   aur agar 0 ho jaaye to map se remove kar dete hain.
5. Jab window me sirf 2 ya usse kam fruit types bachte hain,
   to current window length se maxLen update kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Question basically longest subarray with at most 2 distinct elements hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1) / O(2) practically

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int totalFruits(int[] fruits) {
        //your code goes here
        int l = 0;
        int r = 0;
        int n = fruits.length;
        int maxLen = 0;
        HashMap<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

        while(r < n){
            map.put(fruits[r], map.getOrDefault(fruits[r],0)+1);

            if(map.size() > 2){
                map.put(fruits[l], map.get(fruits[l])-1);
                if(map.get(fruits[l]) == 0) map.remove(fruits[l]);
                l++;
            }
            if(map.size() <= 2){
                maxLen = Math.max(maxLen, r-l+1);
            }
            r++;
        }
        return maxLen;
    }
}
